e to conceive after two years, fecundity is livebirth probability, fecundability is pregnancy probability","Infertility is failure to conceive after six months, fecundity is livebirth probability, fecundability is pregnancy probability","Infertility is failure to conceive after one year, fecundity is pregnancy probability, fecundability is livebirth probability","Infertility is failure to conceive after two years, fecundity is pregnancy probability, fecundability is livebirth probability","Infertility is failure to conceive after one year, fecundity is livebirth probability, fecundability is pregnancy probability"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct definitions are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInfertility\u003C/strong\u003E is the failure to achieve pregnancy after one year of regular unprotected sexual intercourse\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFecundity\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the probability of achieving a live birth from a single menstrual cycle\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFecundability\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the probability of achieving pregnancy from a single menstrual cycle\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options contain incorrect time periods for infertility definition or mix up the definitions of fecundity and fecundability.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Infertility is defined as failure to conceive after one year of unprotected intercourse","Fecundity refers to the probability of achieving a live birth from a single menstrual cycle","Fecundability refers to the probability of achieving pregnancy from a single menstrual cycle"],"references":["Vander Borght M, Wyns C. Fertility and infertility: Definition and epidemiology. Clin Biochem. 2018 Dec;62:2-10. doi: 10.1016/j.clinbiochem.2018.03.012. Epub 2018 Mar 16. PMID: 29555319.","Smarr MM, Sapra KJ, Gemmill A, Kahn LG, Wise LA, Lynch CD,